1
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,830
Episode 18

2
00:00:42,900 --> 00:00:46,540
03/02/1992 Seo Joon Seok Testimony

3
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,270
I've brought the tape.

4
00:01:18,270 --> 00:01:20,290
- Oh, really?
-Yeah.

5
00:01:24,340 --> 00:01:26,540
The testimony is being recorded.

6
00:01:26,540 --> 00:01:33,500
March 2, 1992,
Testimony of Seo Joon Seok

7
00:01:36,870 --> 00:01:40,500
- We heard your father's testimony tape.
- What did he say?

8
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:44,810
Your father, Hyung Joon Seok, wasn't a murder suspect to begin with.

9
00:01:44,810 --> 00:01:47,950
Your father went to the police to report a murder case.

10
00:01:47,950 --> 00:01:51,450
To testify that his friend Oh Gil Han died
in those bastards' hands.

11
00:01:51,450 --> 00:01:56,210
He went to the police with the evidence pictures he took.

12
00:01:57,700 --> 00:02:01,660
So this tape is a witness' testimony,
not a suspect's testimony.

13
00:02:01,660 --> 00:02:03,660
How those bastards killed Hyung Gil Han,

14
00:02:03,660 --> 00:02:06,160
what those bastards were doing on the scene,

15
00:02:06,160 --> 00:02:09,330
your father was talking about those.

16
00:02:17,600 --> 00:02:20,050
Jeong Hoo, I think this much is enough.

17
00:02:20,050 --> 00:02:22,370
Just come back, okay?

18
00:02:22,370 --> 00:02:25,690
This is more than enough to make the broadcast.

19
00:02:25,690 --> 00:02:26,870
What do you think?

20
00:02:26,870 --> 00:02:31,120
Killing my father and making your father a murderer,

21
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:34,830
you're asking me what I think about those bastards who totally screwed our lives?

22
00:02:34,830 --> 00:02:39,700
Let's go according to plan. Let's go all the way till the end.

23
00:02:42,100 --> 00:02:46,000
Another lonely death has occurred.

24
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:50,090
Park Dong Cheol, who got kicked out
of the police station for being a whistle blower,

25
00:02:50,090 --> 00:02:53,800
has kept a cassette tape with him for the last 22 years.

26
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:57,250
It was the very cassette tape with Seo Joon Seok's testimony.

27
00:02:57,250 --> 00:02:59,830
Yeong Sin, throw it!

28
00:02:59,830 --> 00:03:03,440
We suspect that Park Dong Cheol got murdered

29
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:06,410
by the people who want to get rid of that tape.

30
00:03:06,410 --> 00:03:11,040
Because the tape with the testimony from 22 years ago, that he gave Someday before he died,

31
00:03:11,040 --> 00:03:15,000
has an incredible story about them.

32
00:03:17,580 --> 00:03:20,160
Okay, okay. Wait a minute, wait a minute.

33
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:23,500
Take me to meet the Elder.

34
00:03:27,830 --> 00:03:29,750
Ah, he lives in a nice place.

35
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:34,100
Who exactly are "they" who are referred to here?

36
00:03:34,100 --> 00:03:38,260
Our Someday's reporter went to some place
to ask who "they" are.

37
00:03:38,260 --> 00:03:43,050
People usually call him "Elder".

38
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:02,040
Hello.

39
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:05,750
The person whose face you're covering is the Elder, right?

40
00:04:05,750 --> 00:04:07,430
Hello, I'm from Someday News.

41
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:10,160
Can I ask you a question, Elder?

42
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:12,060
Ah, I... can't?

43
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:14,540
These seem to be people working under the Elder!

44
00:04:14,540 --> 00:04:16,160
Wait, let me ask you guys a question.

45
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:19,490
By any chance, would the Elder order you to beat up those reporters in the middle of a live interview,

46
00:04:19,490 --> 00:04:22,450
or whatnot? No, right?

47
00:04:22,450 --> 00:04:25,950
Ah, I'll get scolded if my glasses get damaged. Easy, easy...

48
00:04:32,620 --> 00:04:34,330
This is Park Bong Soo.

49
00:04:34,330 --> 00:04:36,540
There is also a Someday reporter business card.

50
00:04:46,330 --> 00:04:48,480
Didn't you say you were Healer?

51
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,950
If I say it like that...

52
00:04:50,950 --> 00:04:53,450
They said you're going to meet me.

53
00:04:53,450 --> 00:04:58,910
If you're Healer, I'll give you some of my time to talk,

54
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:02,190
- If not...
- Y-y-you'll kill me?

55
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:05,120
I really don't want to die.

56
00:05:05,120 --> 00:05:08,970
Oh right, but Grandfather, are you the Elder?

57
00:05:08,970 --> 00:05:13,950
The one that scumbags like Oh Tae Won, who goes around killing people, work for?

58
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:17,120
If you're curious about that, you can just ask.

59
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:19,060
Why would you take a picture of my face and
put it on a broadcast?

60
00:05:19,060 --> 00:05:23,220
Ah, that... I have no choice.

61
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:27,850
The thing is, if something bothers you,

62
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:30,790
or if they get in your way, you kill them.

63
00:05:30,790 --> 00:05:33,250
But we can't do such things.

64
00:05:33,250 --> 00:05:36,200
This is really unfair.

65
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:39,580
That's why, I should have at least let your face be known

66
00:05:39,580 --> 00:05:41,600
and put a sign under it,

67
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,660
"Beware of a ferocious dog!"

68
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:53,090
Do you think people would thank you?

69
00:05:53,090 --> 00:05:55,540
I can't say. I don't really know.

70
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:59,010
Because this is my first time.

71
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:12,750
Child.

72
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:15,110
Who are you?

73
00:06:15,110 --> 00:06:18,870
Among the people someone like you has killed,

74
00:06:18,870 --> 00:06:21,830
there's a person named Seo Joon Seok.

75
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:27,540
I'm that person's son, Seo Jeong Hoo.

76
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:33,250
Grandfather, from now on when you kill people

77
00:06:33,250 --> 00:06:37,700
it would be good if you would think about their son or daughter.

78
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:43,040
Up until now, you have never thought of that, have you?

79
00:06:48,640 --> 00:06:52,290
Look here, the video's been cut off during the interview in there.

80
00:06:52,290 --> 00:06:54,390
It is this house.

81
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:56,500
Just wait a bit.

82
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,220
We also have to get the order from our superiors...

83
00:06:58,220 --> 00:06:59,800
I'm saying that by the time you get that order,

84
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:03,160
- it's already--
- Just because we're the police, we can't just enter any house on our whim, Miss!

85
00:07:03,160 --> 00:07:07,480
I'm going crazy.

86
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:12,410
Our reporter who has gone inside the Elder's house cannot be reached.

87
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:14,830
Chae Yeong Sin, footage at the Elder's house

88
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:17,330
Ah, a new video has come in just now.

89
00:07:17,330 --> 00:07:20,890
One of our reporters is in front of the house, filming right now.

90
00:07:20,890 --> 00:07:24,620
It also looks like the police have arrived.

91
00:07:51,000 --> 00:07:56,760
It's been a while since a young person has come to this house like this.

92
00:07:56,760 --> 00:07:59,250
Go ahead and sit down there.

93
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,700
Have a cup.

94
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:37,950
I don't drink with someone who killed my father.

95
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:50,450
You're misunderstanding something.

96
00:08:50,450 --> 00:08:54,200
We've never killed anyone.

97
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:57,120
You've probably ordered for them to be killed.

98
00:08:59,450 --> 00:09:03,800
We are all doing the work to save everyone.

99
00:09:03,800 --> 00:09:06,200
How do I explain this to you?

100
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:09,700
From before you keep on saying, 'we, we'.

101
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:14,160
Just exactly how many scumbags like you
are there, Elder?

102
00:09:14,160 --> 00:09:17,810
There is 'us' who look after the people.

103
00:09:17,810 --> 00:09:22,000
There is 'them' who receive our care.

104
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:24,660
Young man,

105
00:09:24,660 --> 00:09:26,910
which side do you want to be on?

106
00:09:26,910 --> 00:09:31,450
Grandfather, you talk too much.

107
00:09:31,450 --> 00:09:37,030
I thought it's going to be someone with such an incredible aura,

108
00:09:40,450 --> 00:09:47,430
but it turned out to be just a talkative grandpa.

109
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:52,990
I'm telling you that I like you a lot, young one.

110
00:09:52,990 --> 00:09:54,940
Think about it.

111
00:09:54,940 --> 00:09:57,700
I won't wait for you for too long.

112
00:10:43,060 --> 00:10:45,290
Testimony is being recorded.

113
00:10:45,290 --> 00:10:49,540
March 2, 1992.

114
00:10:49,540 --> 00:10:52,200
Affiant, Seo Joon Seok.

115
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:57,990
Those people call themselves farmers.

116
00:10:59,390 --> 00:11:02,790
They should be sorry to the real farmers.

117
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:06,860
It's cold.

118
00:11:06,860 --> 00:11:10,170
Us three, myself, Oh Gil Han, and Choi Myeong Hee,

119
00:11:10,170 --> 00:11:13,550
have been following these so-called 'farmers' for a year.

120
00:11:13,550 --> 00:11:17,680
We received information that these people are going to secretly move something using a truck.

121
00:11:17,680 --> 00:11:20,570
We thought they were going to move the slush fund.

122
00:11:21,880 --> 00:11:27,530
These people called farmers, this is what they do.

123
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:34,910
They think our country is their vegetable garden.

124
00:11:36,130 --> 00:11:40,730
They finance political funds and go on some political play that suits their taste.

125
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:45,800
They make the laws they want and reap the benefits from it.

126
00:11:59,690 --> 00:12:03,930
Excuse me, Miss, you can't enter without permission!

127
00:12:18,810 --> 00:12:21,560
Jeong Hoo, what's wrong with you?

128
00:12:21,560 --> 00:12:24,280
Ah, I can't wake up...

129
00:12:25,810 --> 00:12:29,870
Why are you always sleeping when I see you?

130
00:12:29,870 --> 00:12:32,640
But you always wake me up.
♬ With memories of meeting you, a dream like a lie ♬

131
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:36,850
Hmm, did they drug you or something?
Should we go to the hospital?

132
00:12:36,850 --> 00:12:43,400
♬ I will still be waiting here for you ♬

133
00:12:43,400 --> 00:12:49,800
Let me sleep a little more.

134
00:12:49,800 --> 00:12:52,980
♬ When you look at me ♬

135
00:12:52,980 --> 00:12:55,210
Is it him? Is he okay?

136
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:59,770
He's just sleepy.

137
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:04,340
We found him.
♬ Why can't I say anything ♬

138
00:13:06,470 --> 00:13:10,070
- Chae Yeong Sin.
- What? Do you need anything?
♬ when there are so many words I want to say. ♬

139
00:13:10,070 --> 00:13:14,430
Our fathers... they were really close, weren't they?
♬ The moment you turn around ♬

140
00:13:14,430 --> 00:13:18,670
Yeah.
♬ Why are you so distant toward me ♬

141
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:22,480
They say they were on the same side from beginning until the end.
♬ Why is a burst of tears spilling over? ♬

142
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:25,060
You should have seen the broadcast.

143
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:27,510
You tell me about it.
♬ I love you. There's only you. ♬

144
00:13:27,510 --> 00:13:34,970
Excuse me, you, who carries a reporter business card with him, should also watch something called news...

145
00:13:34,970 --> 00:13:37,320
Tell me.
♬ There isn't even anyone else but you ♬

146
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:40,900
♬ Even if I can't touch you, even if I can't hug you ♬

147
00:13:40,900 --> 00:13:44,950
♬ Even if I cry alone, it's okay ♬

148
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:51,570
On that day in 1992, our fathers went out together to do some news gathering.
♬ I will always be looking.  ♬

149
00:13:51,570 --> 00:13:54,350
♬ It's you ♬

150
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:04,290
- Take the pictures well.
- Don't worry, don't worry.

151
00:14:04,290 --> 00:14:06,060
Take good pictures so they are not out of focus.

152
00:14:06,060 --> 00:14:08,450
Have you seen me go out of focus?

153
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:10,970
Hey, I just didn't tell you,
not just once or twice but...

154
00:14:10,970 --> 00:14:13,490
- Hold up! This...
- Awesome, right?

155
00:14:13,490 --> 00:14:15,050
This is the latest model!

156
00:14:15,050 --> 00:14:16,290
- It's expensive, you punk.
- Hold on.

157
00:14:16,290 --> 00:14:18,480
- Hey, hey, hey!
- Stay still!

158
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:20,050
What do you mean stay still?

159
00:14:20,050 --> 00:14:22,790
This guy's crazy!

160
00:14:22,810 --> 00:14:25,030
- Hey, hey, hey
- You are going to break it.

161
00:14:25,880 --> 00:14:27,640
- Let me use it once.
- Hey, you can't!

162
00:14:27,640 --> 00:14:28,980
Just this once.

163
00:14:28,980 --> 00:14:34,680
They just thought it'd be enough to take a photo of the scene of the money exchange.

164
00:14:34,680 --> 00:14:39,630
That's how they set off lightly, thinking they'd be back right away.

165
00:14:53,330 --> 00:14:55,220
What is that?

166
00:15:11,620 --> 00:15:14,060
One apple box contains 200 million won ($200,000).

167
00:15:15,230 --> 00:15:17,330
It looks like there are at least 10.

168
00:15:17,330 --> 00:15:20,100
So one paint truck would be 2 billion won ($2 million)...

169
00:15:21,340 --> 00:15:23,660
I'll take one of those paint cans.

170
00:15:24,470 --> 00:15:25,950
What are you going to do?

171
00:15:25,950 --> 00:15:29,690
You think they'd kill me? I'm still a reporter.

172
00:15:29,690 --> 00:15:31,500
What if they do?

173
00:15:31,500 --> 00:15:33,720
That's impossible, you punk.

174
00:15:36,230 --> 00:15:37,830
What was that?

175
00:15:40,410 --> 00:15:44,120
I'll lure them away. Take one of the paints cans.

176
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:48,260
What are you, bastard? Grab him!

177
00:15:49,550 --> 00:15:51,860
Stop right there, bastard!

178
00:15:56,660 --> 00:15:58,460
Stop there!

179
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:04,070
Oh, wait, wait!

180
00:16:05,210 --> 00:16:08,070
- Hello.
- Who are you?

181
00:16:09,240 --> 00:16:10,340
You can't do that.

182
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:12,570
You can't take that!

183
00:16:12,570 --> 00:16:14,440
Hey!

184
00:16:24,870 --> 00:16:26,090
What's the matter?

185
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:29,850
Gil Han is in danger. So,

186
00:16:29,850 --> 00:16:32,670
Just wait for a moment. I'll go get Gil Han.

187
00:16:32,670 --> 00:16:35,070
Get ready to leave.

188
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:11,650
Ugh!

189
00:17:17,120 --> 00:17:19,900
Let me go! Hey!

190
00:17:21,360 --> 00:17:22,430
Hurry!

191
00:17:22,430 --> 00:17:24,880
Gil Han! Gil Han.

192
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:28,190
- Gil Han...
- Seo Joon Seok!

193
00:17:28,190 --> 00:17:31,240
We have to go. Hurry.

194
00:17:34,160 --> 00:17:36,130
Gil Han.

195
00:17:36,130 --> 00:17:38,570
Gil Han!

196
00:17:50,590 --> 00:17:52,500
Take down the plate number.

197
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,010
Yes.

198
00:17:55,090 --> 00:18:00,440
While fleeing for a few days,
I tried to figure out what that paint was.

199
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:10,100
This is a fake red lead.

200
00:18:12,510 --> 00:18:15,040
In construction, if you pour it on the steel frame,

201
00:18:16,140 --> 00:18:19,030
the corrosion of the steel gets accelerated.

202
00:18:22,180 --> 00:18:25,450
Usually, we want to slow down the rusting,

203
00:18:27,380 --> 00:18:30,630
but this is made for the exact opposite!

204
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:38,040
Excuse me.

205
00:18:44,550 --> 00:18:47,700
That's how the recording in the tape ended.

206
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:53,450
Those old men (our parents)...
they have lived an exhausting life.

207
00:18:53,450 --> 00:18:55,560
It looks that way.

208
00:18:57,160 --> 00:18:59,390
It's over.

209
00:18:59,390 --> 00:19:00,470
What?

210
00:19:00,470 --> 00:19:07,530
Assignment. Teacher. Father. And you.

211
00:19:13,430 --> 00:19:15,930
Good job.

212
00:19:27,130 --> 00:19:29,360
- Yeong Sin.
- Yeah?

213
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:32,100
I was thinking while sleeping...

214
00:19:32,100 --> 00:19:33,710
How can you think while sleeping?

215
00:19:33,710 --> 00:19:38,040
Living like everyone else... Is it hard?

216
00:19:40,110 --> 00:19:42,760
You want to live like that? Like other people?

217
00:19:42,760 --> 00:19:45,670
Would it be hard for me?

218
00:19:47,380 --> 00:19:50,690
Let's try it. Living like others.

219
00:19:50,690 --> 00:19:52,660
You'll stay by my side, right?

220
00:19:52,660 --> 00:19:54,500
Of course.

221
00:19:55,020 --> 00:19:57,420
Good.

222
00:20:19,110 --> 00:20:22,780
I thought you set Ji An's birthday table.

223
00:20:22,780 --> 00:20:25,990
I did a simple one at lunchtime.

224
00:20:25,990 --> 00:20:28,720
Weren't you sick then?

225
00:20:28,720 --> 00:20:32,170
It was short, just passing through.

226
00:20:39,320 --> 00:20:41,700
Don't be sick.

227
00:20:42,790 --> 00:20:45,380
I'm not going to be sick now.

228
00:20:57,330 --> 00:21:00,170
I watched Moon Ho's broadcast.

229
00:21:02,260 --> 00:21:05,340
I would have preferred that you didn't.

230
00:21:05,340 --> 00:21:09,410
But, were you all right

231
00:21:09,410 --> 00:21:11,540
watching something like that?

232
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:17,360
How much have you known? The details you never told me?

233
00:21:18,120 --> 00:21:21,470
There isn't any part I didn't tell you.

234
00:21:24,990 --> 00:21:30,190
That day I was waiting in the car, and after Joon Seok came running over, he told me to escape. And

235
00:21:30,190 --> 00:21:33,610
I took him and escaped. Although I haven't said anything,

236
00:21:33,610 --> 00:21:36,990
actually, up to now, I have been suspicious of Joon Seok.

237
00:21:36,990 --> 00:21:39,750
It's a relief to clear up my misunderstanding.

238
00:21:45,260 --> 00:21:50,020
This soup is delicious. Is it consommé?

239
00:21:56,030 --> 00:22:00,050
It's a new recipe I tried. Is it good?

240
00:22:43,340 --> 00:22:48,190
Close your eyes just once. And open them again.

241
00:22:48,190 --> 00:22:53,530
Then the invisible is made visible.

242
00:22:55,570 --> 00:23:00,600
That is called... growing up.

243
00:23:06,790 --> 00:23:12,300
I... saw it.

244
00:23:12,300 --> 00:23:14,930
Joon Seok killed

245
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:19,500
Gil Han.

246
00:23:25,980 --> 00:23:32,340
We were tailing the truck which had the slush fund.

247
00:23:33,080 --> 00:23:38,900
The truck driver saw us arrive at the scene and fled.

248
00:23:39,590 --> 00:23:44,530
When the truck door was opened, there was a box full of 10,000 won notes ...

249
00:23:45,430 --> 00:23:48,210
We had a fight in front of the money.

250
00:23:48,210 --> 00:23:53,270
"This money has no owner, let's take it."
"We can't do that."

251
00:23:53,270 --> 00:23:58,210
