00:40:54,400 --> 00:40:57,510
It's alright, relax, please.

502
00:40:58,830 --> 00:41:03,540
Chief Kang. You can ask anything you want to ask.

503
00:41:07,790 --> 00:41:12,750
These days, regarding the conflict
between me and my brother, Reporter Kim,

504
00:41:12,750 --> 00:41:15,240
I heard some people call it, "War between brothers".
I'm well aware of it.

505
00:41:15,240 --> 00:41:17,910
(Ed. note : "War Among Brothers" refers to Joseon's third king, King Taejong who killed his brothers for the throne.)

506
00:41:17,910 --> 00:41:21,270
Yes, because of the very same reason,
there are some voices of concern

507
00:41:21,270 --> 00:41:26,080
that doubt if you can take care of Seoul properly
while you can't even handle your own family.

508
00:41:26,080 --> 00:41:30,290
Yes, I know.
My brother and I, both of us are journalists.

509
00:41:30,290 --> 00:41:33,450
It was the 80's when I first became a journalist.

510
00:41:33,450 --> 00:41:39,250
My brother, Reporter Kim Moon Ho, recently aired the broadcast series about this story and gained some popularity.

511
00:41:39,250 --> 00:41:44,020
You know the pirate broadcasting team mentioned in that show? I was a member of it.

512
00:41:44,020 --> 00:41:49,000
I brought a photo today,
but I'm not sure if I can show it to you here.

513
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:51,410
- Yes, I want to see it.
- Okay.

514
00:41:51,410 --> 00:41:54,410
Where... Ah.

515
00:41:54,410 --> 00:41:57,250
Among these five friends,
here, this is me.

516
00:41:57,250 --> 00:42:00,430
Next to me, this is my wife now.

517
00:42:00,430 --> 00:42:05,160
I fought for the freedom of speech
even during that harsh era (of censorship).

518
00:42:05,160 --> 00:42:09,290
So, even if my brother makes some contrary reports,

519
00:42:09,290 --> 00:42:10,930
I should cut him some slack

520
00:42:10,930 --> 00:42:17,120
because that is how we observe the freedom of speech
which we have fought for and protected.

521
00:42:17,120 --> 00:42:19,480
The concept of the pirate broadcasting
is actually a bit unfamiliar to us...

522
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:25,330
- Could you explain more? 
- The content of their show totally changed,
so what about our delayed spiking broadcasting?

523
00:42:25,330 --> 00:42:27,300
- In the 80's, the forbidden words, ...
- I'm cancelling it.

524
00:42:27,300 --> 00:42:31,760
... and the contents we couldn't broadcast,
there were so many of them.

525
00:42:31,760 --> 00:42:37,000
So, we had no choice but to make pirate broadcasts.

526
00:42:37,000 --> 00:42:41,700
Frankly speaking, nowadays, we're enjoying the freedom of speech excessively, don't you think so?

527
00:42:41,700 --> 00:42:47,290
For the freedom you're enjoying today,
the previous generation made a sacrifice.

528
00:42:47,290 --> 00:42:51,100
I wish the viewers acknowledge that point.

529
00:42:51,100 --> 00:42:55,450
Honestly, I was a bit surprised
that Candidate Kim Moon Sik, CEO of Je Il Newspaper,

530
00:42:55,450 --> 00:42:58,350
used to make a pirate broadcast.

531
00:42:58,350 --> 00:43:01,030
I have something I want to show you.

532
00:43:02,090 --> 00:43:04,330
What is it?

533
00:43:11,830 --> 00:43:15,330
What is that?
Those are yours, Boss.

534
00:43:16,290 --> 00:43:20,850
These are the cassette tapes of the broadcasts
that our pirate broadcasting team worked on.

535
00:43:20,850 --> 00:43:25,120
I have kept them dearly for more than twenty years.

536
00:43:25,120 --> 00:43:30,530
Here, can you see the date on it?
Marked as 1980, you can see it, right?

537
00:43:32,140 --> 00:43:35,910
Can you see this magazine printed by stencil pen?

538
00:43:35,910 --> 00:43:38,290
This might look a bit shabby
to the young people nowadays,

539
00:43:38,290 --> 00:43:42,430
but we were really innocent back then, like this.

540
00:43:42,430 --> 00:43:45,120
Was it made by that pirate broadcasting team?

541
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:49,830
Yes, it was published just once back then.

542
00:43:49,830 --> 00:43:53,530
The name of the magazine is Healer.
What does that mean?

543
00:43:55,270 --> 00:43:57,050
Look right here.

544
00:43:57,050 --> 00:44:02,450
Media exists to diagnose
the pain of this society and cure it.

545
00:44:03,700 --> 00:44:08,040
With this mindset, I have protected the media so far.

546
00:44:09,390 --> 00:44:15,130
I, who am such a person, am now going
to dedicate this mind to Seoul.

547
00:44:15,130 --> 00:44:23,970
For the freedom, democracy and order we've protected by devoting our lives.

548
00:44:32,430 --> 00:44:35,330
Are you all right?

549
00:44:38,450 --> 00:44:40,200
I'm sorry.

550
00:44:40,200 --> 00:44:43,500
For what?

551
00:44:43,500 --> 00:44:45,540
I'm sorry.

552
00:44:49,870 --> 00:44:54,620
Please don't cry. Otherwise, you'll get sick again.

553
00:44:54,620 --> 00:44:58,540
Was something... something wrong?

554
00:45:25,660 --> 00:45:30,660
Those tapes, if those bastards stole them,
do you want me to bring them back?

555
00:45:30,660 --> 00:45:32,210
That's not that difficult, you know.

556
00:45:32,210 --> 00:45:36,300
You said you wouldn't do that kind of work any longer.
I thought you wanted to live like other people.

557
00:45:36,300 --> 00:45:38,670
Ah... You must have heard that from Yeong Sin.

558
00:45:40,370 --> 00:45:45,250
That's right. I also hope you can live like that.

559
00:45:45,250 --> 00:45:48,600
Well, about that, I will take care of it myself, but...

560
00:45:49,700 --> 00:45:52,390
Are you all right?

561
00:45:52,390 --> 00:45:55,250
I was really scared that you might cry.

562
00:45:55,250 --> 00:45:57,320
I almost cried.

563
00:45:58,100 --> 00:46:01,370
Because those tapes were stolen?

564
00:46:02,120 --> 00:46:04,500
Some day, come with some beer again,

565
00:46:04,500 --> 00:46:06,870
I have a lot of stories I want to tell you.

566
00:46:06,870 --> 00:46:09,040
Together with Yeong Sin?

567
00:46:09,040 --> 00:46:11,050
All right.

568
00:46:19,500 --> 00:46:23,250
Those guys I have are the world's top class
in terms of their skills.

569
00:46:23,250 --> 00:46:26,330
- Besides, ...
- For the time being, I will use this room.

570
00:46:26,330 --> 00:46:28,910
Over there, please set up one more desk.

571
00:46:28,910 --> 00:46:32,540
You have another place to stay,
other than this room, right?

572
00:46:32,540 --> 00:46:35,230
Me? Other than this room?

573
00:46:35,230 --> 00:46:36,880
Set up as soon as the desk is ready.

574
00:46:36,880 --> 00:46:38,950
I understand.

575
00:46:38,950 --> 00:46:41,660
I guess you don't know who I am.

576
00:46:41,660 --> 00:46:45,040
Look here! I'm Bae Sang Soo,
CEO of this place!

577
00:46:45,040 --> 00:46:48,370
So, Double S! From the initials of my name, S and S!

578
00:46:48,370 --> 00:46:50,720
And, this room!

579
00:46:50,720 --> 00:46:52,340
This is the CEO's office, you know.

580
00:46:52,340 --> 00:46:54,300
Calling - Phone connect.

581
00:46:54,300 --> 00:46:56,700
Hello.

582
00:46:58,090 --> 00:47:00,200
From the Double S, the people are coming out.

583
00:47:00,200 --> 00:47:02,950
Those guys killed all CCTVs nearby that.

584
00:47:02,950 --> 00:47:05,080
You should take photos and send me those.

585
00:47:09,620 --> 00:47:12,620
Take a picture of the license plate number.

586
00:47:16,650 --> 00:47:17,900
Shall I follow them?

587
00:47:17,900 --> 00:47:19,840
Never mind. Just stand by.

588
00:47:19,840 --> 00:47:23,080
By the way, what are we now chasing after here?

589
00:47:23,080 --> 00:47:26,330
We're now in the middle of making
the severance package for Healer.

590
00:47:26,330 --> 00:47:30,160
Those guys who followed Healer,
starting from Park Dong Cheol's place.

591
00:47:30,160 --> 00:47:34,040
Healer took photos of them, like this.

592
00:47:34,040 --> 00:47:39,400
So, among these punks, I think there must be
the real murderer who killed Park Dong Cheol.

593
00:47:40,260 --> 00:47:43,540
Why are they hanging out with Sang Soo's gang...?

594
00:47:53,450 --> 00:47:55,750
Where did I see this guy...?

595
00:47:55,750 --> 00:47:58,120
I'm sure I've seen him before...

596
00:48:07,410 --> 00:48:11,350
This is Someday. Yes, we're looking
for any information regarding to the Elder.

597
00:48:11,350 --> 00:48:13,580
The phone number of night snack place...?

598
00:48:13,580 --> 00:48:16,540
I don't really know that.

599
00:48:23,050 --> 00:48:27,900
Well, among the posts on the message boards,
about 70% of them are just pranks,

600
00:48:27,900 --> 00:48:31,910
and 20% are irrelevant.

601
00:48:31,910 --> 00:48:34,410
But still, we had more gains than we expected.

602
00:48:34,410 --> 00:48:38,500
We have already got two, three tips
about the Seodo Bridge case.

603
00:48:38,500 --> 00:48:43,040
But about that, there must have been
some emotional impact to the laborers back then.

604
00:48:43,040 --> 00:48:46,830
Just think about it, please.
The bridge they had worked on just collapsed.

605
00:48:46,830 --> 00:48:51,830
What could've happened if it collapsed
after it was open to traffic?

606
00:48:51,830 --> 00:48:56,870
Oh dear, you should have some sleep.
It seems you hardly went to sleep.

607
00:48:56,870 --> 00:48:59,550
I think it's time to start soon.

608
00:49:00,250 --> 00:49:03,880
From where and how they would come at us,
frankly speaking, I have no clue.

609
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:08,950
I see. But, they are good at only one thing.

610
00:49:08,950 --> 00:49:11,700
They will probably start from taking up our "spoons".
(Editor's Note : "spoons" - implying "livelihood")

611
00:49:11,700 --> 00:49:14,700
It's too dirty and petty
that I don't even want to fight against them.

612
00:49:14,700 --> 00:49:18,290
But its effectiveness is really something. Jeez.

613
00:50:09,030 --> 00:50:11,600
You guys sure are confident.

614
00:50:12,770 --> 00:50:15,250
Chae Yeong Sin can't sleep in places with other people.

615
00:50:15,250 --> 00:50:19,270
- How about you?
- I am not 'other people'.

616
00:50:21,140 --> 00:50:22,690
Look here.

617
00:50:26,590 --> 00:50:29,280
Ah, I really hate leaving pictures...

618
00:50:29,280 --> 00:50:32,980
I have liked taking pictures
ever since I first started walking.

619
00:50:38,490 --> 00:50:41,390
- But...
- Yeah.

620
00:50:41,390 --> 00:50:44,950
You're fighting against that person called Elder right now, right?

621
00:50:44,950 --> 00:50:46,860
Right.

622
00:50:46,860 --> 00:50:50,680
- Will Yeong Sin be in danger again?
- I don't know.

623
00:50:51,510 --> 00:50:57,590
Do you want to take her far from here? If you go, it would be easier to live like other people.

624
00:50:58,620 --> 00:51:01,300
I'm wavering.

625
00:51:01,300 --> 00:51:03,070
Why?

626
00:51:03,070 --> 00:51:06,240
I thought about why I'm hesitating.

627
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:08,920
It looks like it's because of you.

628
00:51:09,740 --> 00:51:15,110
It just bothers me a bit if the two of us go and leave you alone.

629
00:51:16,380 --> 00:51:18,910
I'm touched.

630
00:51:19,930 --> 00:51:22,860
- But...
- Yeah.

631
00:51:22,860 --> 00:51:28,510
I can't be without her. If it's for her, I can abandon you.

632
00:51:28,510 --> 00:51:30,210
It's okay.

633
00:51:50,670 --> 00:51:54,600
Yes, you called the wrong number.

634
00:51:54,600 --> 00:51:57,620
This is Someday News. Are you giving us a report?

635
00:51:57,620 --> 00:52:01,490
We need to record the reports we receive. Is that fine with you?

636
00:52:01,490 --> 00:52:03,190
Ah, yes.

637
00:52:06,670 --> 00:52:08,890
Wait one moment.

638
00:52:10,460 --> 00:52:12,730
Please tell me.

639
00:52:12,730 --> 00:52:14,790
Here's the mail.

640
00:52:19,810 --> 00:52:21,470
Media Control Agency

641
00:52:21,500 --> 00:52:23,300
Summons for mediation committee

642
00:52:23,300 --> 00:52:25,110
Here.

643
00:52:25,910 --> 00:52:28,890
Something came from the Prosecutor.

644
00:52:33,040 --> 00:52:34,900
Prosecutor
Summons

645
00:52:34,900 --> 00:52:36,620
Summons

646
00:52:36,620 --> 00:52:38,680
Summons

647
00:52:38,680 --> 00:52:41,980
The informant should be able to introduce people whom he worked with back then.

648
00:52:41,980 --> 00:52:43,860
Start out first by putting them at their ease.

649
00:52:43,860 --> 00:52:45,980
Yes, I understand.

650
00:52:46,650 --> 00:52:50,460
Oh, wait. Who are you? Where did you come from?

651
00:52:50,460 --> 00:52:53,170
We are from the National Tax Service,
Seoul Branch's Audit Group 4.

652
00:52:53,170 --> 00:52:55,280
National Tax Service ...

653
00:52:55,280 --> 00:52:57,460
What's going on?

654
00:52:57,460 --> 00:53:02,070
A tip came in making allegations regarding the source of the funds for the acquisition of Someday News.

655
00:53:02,070 --> 00:53:03,520
Mr. Kim Moon Ho?

656
00:53:04,170 --> 00:53:08,110
- Yes, that's me.
- If you agree to it, we will start the search and seizure process right away.

657
00:53:08,110 --> 00:53:11,610
If you object, we will do a compulsory search.

658
00:53:19,670 --> 00:53:21,580
I understand.

659
00:53:21,580 --> 00:53:24,000
Oh, you can't do this!

660
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:26,820
Wait, wait, wait!

661
00:53:26,820 --> 00:53:29,210
Please cooperate with us.

662
00:53:29,210 --> 00:53:32,110
I bought that with my own money. With my own money!

663
00:53:32,110 --> 00:53:33,460
Give it to me.

664
00:53:33,460 --> 00:53:37,220
Well, it's mine. I'm telling you this is mine.

665
00:53:37,220 --> 00:53:38,930
Ah, seriously.

666
00:53:53,500 --> 00:53:58,210
- Excuse me...
- Yeah? Ow, that hurt.
- Why... Is there...?

667
00:53:58,210 --> 00:54:01,680
No, no. It's nothing.

668
00:54:05,460 --> 00:54:07,560
Hey, Bong Soo.

669
00:54:07,560 --> 00:54:10,880
-Yes?
- My wife owns a chicken restaurant.

670
00:54:10,880 --> 00:54:14,130
But the business license got suspended after the city health inspection

671
00:54:14,130 --> 00:54:18,050
that claims to have found bacteria in the water filter.

672
00:54:18,050 --> 00:54:22,850
And the fine was over 10 million won ($10,000).

673
00:54:22,850 --> 00:54:27,920
That couldn't be related to our Someday, could it?

674
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:34,500
Never mind. Just go on.

675
00:54:36,340 --> 00:54:38,630
It probably isn't... Aigoo...

676
00:55:41,860 --> 00:55:43,200
What?

677
00:55:44,960 --> 00:55:48,270
It's weird. That car.

678
00:56:18,620 --> 00:56:20,700
What's going on?

679
00:56:24,550 --> 00:56:27,930
Ahjumma, can you track Kim Moon Ho's cellphone?

680
00:56:27,930 --> 00:56:30,820
Forget about being retired or getting fired! Please!

681
00:56:33,680 --> 00:56:35,690
I think he's been kidnapped.

682
00:56:37,290 --> 00:56:41,300
What do you want to do? Do you want to come with me, or do you want to wait inside Kim Moon Ho's house, or-

683
00:56:41,300 --> 00:56:45,010
If you go, you'll be fighting again, right?

684
00:56:45,010 --> 00:56:46,700
Probably.

685
00:56:50,300 --> 00:56:53,150
Go, and bring Sunbae back.

686
00:56:58,650 --> 00:57:01,790
- Let's go.
- What are you doing? Hurry and go.

687
00:57:01,790 --> 00:57:05,400
Alright. You know the code for Kim Moon Ho's house, right?

688
00:57:05,400 --> 00:57:09,930
- By the entrance, there's a latch. You have to...
- I get it already, just go.

689
00:57:57,870 --> 00:58:01,230
A right turn on the incoming intersection.
